Table 2 presents the best IS (resp., FID) obtained by the algorithms on MNIST and Fashion MNIST (resp., CelebA) given a fixed amount of communication for each dataset.
The results show that CDMA-ADA (resp., CDMA-ONE) achieves the best (resp., second best) performance among the compared algorithms.

Figure 4 and Figures 6-8 complement the results of Table 2.
In Figure 4, we present the training curve of each algorithm.
In Figures 6-8, we visualize sample images generated by all the compared algorithms after training.
We can see that both CDMA-ONE and CDMA-ADA generate high-quality sample images.
